criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  age 18 to 50;

          -  a CP diagnosis at least for the last three months;

          -  access to internet and willingness to do it regularly (at least once a week)

          -  willingness to be randomized

          -  provide informed consent.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  undergoing any other form of psychological intervention for CP;

          -  severe psychiatric problem (e.g. severe depression; psychotic illness; bipolar
             disorder; borderline personality disorder), assessed using several questions
             (self-reported) based on the diagnostic criteria according to DSM-V;

          -  pain due to malignancy, trauma, or surgery.
